{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Urgently review Advisory Electricity Rate (AER) for fully electric company cars",
        "additional_details": "This shortfall discourages use of fully electric company cars. The Government should urgently review the current AER. It should also commit to reviewing the AER quarterly in future, as they do for fossil fuels in the Advisory Fuel Rates, and ensure the AER is not based on the lowest available domestic overnight tariff. For example, it would be fairer if the AER were set at the mid-point between the average of the cost of charging on a domestic tariff and on public rapid charging points.",
        "background": "Since the energy price cap increase, domestic electricity costs ~28p/kWh. If a car\u2019s efficiency is 2.8-4.0 miles/kWh, the cost per mile is 7p-10p. The average cost at a public charging point is 44.5p/kWh (~11p-16p per mile). HMRC\u2019s AER is just 5p per mile. HMRC should urgently consider raising this.",
